pair O = (0,r), P = (3,1), T = interp(O,P,r/(r + 1));

draw((-4,0)--(4,0));
draw(Circle(P,1));
draw(Circle((-3,1),1));
draw(Circle(O,r));
draw(O--(0,0));
draw(O--P);
draw((3,1)--(0,1));
draw((3,1)--(3,0));

label("$r$", (O + T)/2, N);
label("$1$", (T + P)/2, N);
label("$1$", (3,1/2), E);
label("$1$", (0,1/2), W);
label("$r - 1$", (0,(r + 1)/2), W);
label("$3$", (3/2,0), S);

dot("$O$", O, N);
dot("$P$", P, NE);
[/asy]

Projecting $P$ onto the $z$-axis, we obtain a right triangle with legs 3 and $r - 1,$ and hypotenuse $r + 1.$  Then by the Pythagorean Theorem,
\[3 + (r - 1)^2 = (r + 1)^2.\]Solving, we find $r=\boxed{\frac{9}{4}}$.

